WEBVTT

00:06.073 --> 00:09.510
Everybody's gonna be
pumped to see the plate man.

00:09.543 --> 00:11.078
No, they're not, baby.

00:11.111 --> 00:12.672
Oh, here comes the plate man!

00:12.672 --> 00:14.107
Can't have a barbecue without plates!

00:14.140 --> 00:15.608
Uncle George, look at this!

00:15.642 --> 00:17.577
Paper bowls for dips, sides.

00:17.610 --> 00:19.612
Hey, hey! Plate man!

00:19.646 --> 00:22.582
- Hi, Mom.
- Chrissy, you look

00:22.615 --> 00:24.815
- beautiful in purple.
- My baby.

00:25.018 --> 00:27.454
And look at Tim. Don't you look cute.

00:27.487 --> 00:29.105
Oh, thank you.

00:29.105 --> 00:32.107
- Yeah, he knows.
- Hi, David! George!

00:32.142 --> 00:33.243
Aww...

00:33.675 --> 00:34.811
Sam's here.

00:37.423 --> 00:38.715
Who's he with?

00:40.270 --> 00:41.726
Sam, who are you with? Who are you?

00:42.108 --> 00:43.186
Uh, I'm Shannon.

00:43.219 --> 00:44.254
This is Shannon, Tim.

00:44.287 --> 00:45.755
Hi, Shannon. Who are you?

00:46.174 --> 00:47.808
She's my girlfriend.

00:48.475 --> 00:49.599
Girlfriend?

00:50.825 --> 00:51.898
Since when?

00:52.040 --> 00:54.315
Ah, feels like a day,
it's been so much fun.

00:54.348 --> 00:56.317
- How long?
- I don't know.

00:56.350 --> 00:57.785
It's been a blur, it's been so much fun.

00:57.818 --> 01:00.354
- How long?
- It's been a blur.

01:00.388 --> 01:01.789
- How long?
- A month!

01:01.822 --> 01:03.346
A whole friggin' month!

01:03.346 --> 01:05.382
You've had a girlfriend
that you've hid from me

01:05.416 --> 01:07.416
- for a month?
- I know!

01:07.985 --> 01:09.186
Well, technically, babe,

01:09.220 --> 01:10.671
it's about five weeks.

01:11.622 --> 01:14.538
Tim, it's your own friggin' fault, okay?

01:14.538 --> 01:17.842
I... you can be difficult
to introduce new people to.

01:18.364 --> 01:19.800
- Why?
- Why?

01:19.898 --> 01:21.538
This guy says "why?"

01:21.722 --> 01:24.381
Because, Tim, you can be a little harsh.

01:24.552 --> 01:26.514
Harsh?

01:27.088 --> 01:28.089
Harsh?

01:28.704 --> 01:30.024
Okay, Shannon, how are you?

01:30.344 --> 01:31.445
- Uh...
- You look lovely.

01:31.478 --> 01:32.813
Is that blouse from Ann Taylor?

01:32.846 --> 01:34.515
- No.
- Well, someone should tell

01:34.548 --> 01:36.288
Ann Taylor, because they
have a very similar one.

01:36.462 --> 01:37.998
What are you even
trying to go for with this?

01:37.998 --> 01:39.700
I shop for Chrissy at Ann Taylor.

01:40.369 --> 01:42.705
I'm just saying, I think
they'd be very interested

01:42.738 --> 01:44.883
in knowing that someone's
selling a cheaper version.

01:45.107 --> 01:46.509
How do you know this one's cheaper?

01:46.542 --> 01:49.812
'Cause I shop for Chrissy
at Ann Taylor, idiot!

01:49.845 --> 01:51.747
It could be nicer, dillweed.

01:51.781 --> 01:54.116
It's... not!

01:54.553 --> 01:56.027
Um, nice to meet you, Tim.

01:56.052 --> 01:57.879
I've... heard lots about you.

01:58.775 --> 02:00.248
All good things, I'm sure.

02:00.898 --> 02:01.884
Yeah.

02:02.488 --> 02:03.937
- Let's go say hi to my mom.
- Okay.

02:03.962 --> 02:05.003
- What did you bring, slop?
- No.

02:05.028 --> 02:05.970
Come on, now.

