02:21.580 --> 02:22.915
Oh, my God, it's Shannon Coyne.

02:22.940 --> 02:24.009
- That's Shannon Coyne.
- You got to be cool.

02:24.034 --> 02:25.146
I'm being cool.

02:25.171 --> 02:28.466
Wow, Shannon Coyne.

02:28.655 --> 02:31.391
Oh, we grew up listening to
your family's gospel music.

02:31.424 --> 02:32.826
- Thank you.
- So what's it like

02:32.859 --> 02:34.260
dating a celebrity?

02:34.294 --> 02:35.795
Oh, I don't know, babe. What's it like?

02:35.829 --> 02:37.234
Oh, Sam.

02:37.234 --> 02:39.270
- She's talking about me.
- I know, I was joking.

02:39.303 --> 02:40.537
How do you get up in
front of all those people?

02:40.571 --> 02:42.239
I would be so scared.

02:42.273 --> 02:44.475
You know, actually I have stage fright,

02:44.508 --> 02:46.479
so I get up there

02:46.978 --> 02:48.913
and I close my eyes

02:49.379 --> 02:53.250
and I...

02:55.366 --> 02:57.285
Yeah, would you like to take a selfie?

02:58.236 --> 02:59.473
You know who that is?

02:59.976 --> 03:01.506
That's Sam's girlfriend.

03:01.539 --> 03:02.548
Hm.

03:03.441 --> 03:05.706
I know. He hid it from me for a month

03:05.706 --> 03:07.580
because I'm too harsh.

03:08.174 --> 03:09.929
Well, Tim, you can be harsh.

03:10.247 --> 03:12.390
Maybe Sam just want to
build something first

03:12.390 --> 03:13.709
before you bulldozed it.

03:13.709 --> 03:15.073
Bulldozed it?

03:15.811 --> 03:19.364
I have been nothing but lovely
to all Sam's girlfriends.

03:20.203 --> 03:23.073
I was a perfect gentleman
to Dump Truck Debra.

03:23.655 --> 03:25.084
I've been nice to all of them.

03:25.490 --> 03:27.771
Stupid Sarah, Dumb Beth,

03:27.771 --> 03:29.541
Debbie "The Animal" Steel, the Worm.

03:29.541 --> 03:32.244
- Tim.
- I was so nice to the Worm.

03:32.278 --> 03:33.446
Would you listen to yourself?

03:33.479 --> 03:34.814
You're harsh as hell.

03:34.847 --> 03:37.461
Okay, if it's because I'm too harsh,

03:37.750 --> 03:40.286
then how come he kept it a
secret from the whole family.

03:40.806 --> 03:42.161
He didn't tell your parents,

03:42.199 --> 03:44.231
Aunt Lacey, your grandma, you.

03:46.031 --> 03:47.146
Holy shit.

03:47.733 --> 03:48.878
You knew.

03:50.636 --> 03:52.355
Oh, my God, you all knew.

03:52.833 --> 03:55.202
The whole family knew, and they lied to me.

03:55.322 --> 03:56.623
They lied to my face!

03:56.657 --> 03:58.692
- Well...
- You're a family of liars!

03:59.039 --> 04:01.175
Big, fake liars!

04:02.646 --> 04:03.744
Liar!

04:04.201 --> 04:06.276
- Hey, girl!
- I love your hair.

04:09.750 --> 04:11.735
Welcome, welcome, one and all

04:11.735 --> 04:14.004
to the Duvet family reunion!

04:15.939 --> 04:17.974
We got drinks and, of course,

04:18.007 --> 04:20.543
we've got the annual basketball game,

04:20.577 --> 04:24.007
which my team has won six years in a row.

04:25.039 --> 04:26.950
Now listen, over 30 years ago,

04:27.584 --> 04:30.743
I took over the position as
grill master from my father.

04:31.159 --> 04:32.903
Today it gives me great honor

04:33.097 --> 04:35.122
to pass this on to my son,

04:35.273 --> 04:36.425
Samuel!

04:37.968 --> 04:39.716
Have you all met his new girlfriend?

04:39.755 --> 04:41.156
Shannon Coyne!

04:41.190 --> 04:42.307
Yes!

04:42.858 --> 04:45.869
Good looks, personality, and lineage.

04:46.128 --> 04:49.198
Yes, I'm telling you,
she is the total package.

04:49.231 --> 04:50.832
And she's a celebrity.

04:50.832 --> 04:51.934
Come on up here, son.

04:58.540 --> 05:00.042
Ah. Thanks, Dad.

05:00.477 --> 05:01.971
You know, this is an honor

05:01.971 --> 05:04.168
I've waited for my entire life.

05:04.356 --> 05:07.330
In fact, when I was 7, I wrote a speech

05:07.792 --> 05:09.141
I bring with me every reunion.

05:09.475 --> 05:11.295
- Should I read it?
- Yes!

05:11.329 --> 05:13.164
- Should I read it?
- Yes!

05:13.198 --> 05:15.433
- Should I read this here speech?
- Yes!

05:15.467 --> 05:17.854
Well, if you insist.

05:18.594 --> 05:21.297
"Friends, Duvets, and guests,

05:21.329 --> 05:24.299
"I am honored to be your grill master.

05:24.696 --> 05:26.532
"It's an achievement I rank up there

05:26.565 --> 05:28.100
with my black belt in tae kwon do"...

05:28.133 --> 05:29.736
Oop, never did that.

05:30.469 --> 05:32.029
Let's see. Oop.

05:32.504 --> 05:33.588
Never did that.

05:35.002 --> 05:36.988
"Quick thank you to Grandpa Charles."

05:37.971 --> 05:40.045
He's dead. Sad.

05:40.078 --> 05:41.780
Uh, didn't do that.

05:42.226 --> 05:43.554
"Marry Mom"?

05:43.882 --> 05:45.676
I was 7, again,

05:45.676 --> 05:47.031
when I wrote this, so...

05:47.827 --> 05:50.214
Still seems kind of old to want to do that.

05:50.247 --> 05:53.181
Really should have looked over
this at some point since then.

05:53.551 --> 05:56.436
Oh, "And never getting in a car"

05:56.484 --> 05:57.851
with a stranger"

05:58.106 --> 06:00.241
'cause stranger danger."

06:00.504 --> 06:01.656
Hmm? Never did that.

06:01.656 --> 06:03.888
So... and you shouldn't,
so that's a good thing.

06:04.041 --> 06:05.209
Kids, learn from it.

06:05.243 --> 06:06.352
Ah, thank you!

06:06.352 --> 06:07.475
Uh, yep.

06:08.488 --> 06:10.007
Thank you very much, son.

06:12.435 --> 06:13.459
All right.

06:13.852 --> 06:15.453
I hope your bellies are empty

06:15.628 --> 06:17.336
and you're ready for fun,

06:17.530 --> 06:20.032
because the Duvet family reunion

06:20.066 --> 06:22.101
has officially begun!

06:29.396 --> 06:30.722
Medium rare for the gentleman.

06:31.878 --> 06:33.239
And for the lady...

06:33.433 --> 06:35.258
- Ooh!
- Well done.

06:35.258 --> 06:37.494
- All right, man.
- Ange, you want a hot dog?

06:40.459 --> 06:42.416
Whoo! Now that's a hot dog.

06:42.450 --> 06:44.042
Am I right? Am I right?

06:44.498 --> 06:45.576
Here you go.

06:46.021 --> 06:47.989
You know your dad was
supposed to be pass long

06:48.022 --> 06:49.190
grill master to me.

06:49.612 --> 06:51.547
But, see, I just quit drinking,

06:51.581 --> 06:53.349
and so I got the shakes,

06:53.549 --> 06:55.283
but I'm happier, healthier.

06:55.476 --> 06:57.764
Oh! What you got there, man?

06:58.846 --> 07:00.332
That smell like Crown Royal.

07:01.391 --> 07:03.162
Ladies, may I?

07:03.162 --> 07:04.730
Of course, sweetie. Come on.

07:05.504 --> 07:07.073
No paper bowls, huh?

07:07.106 --> 07:08.489
Just cream corn touching everything?

07:08.490 --> 07:10.674
Oh, we were just talking
about how nice it is

07:10.699 --> 07:13.421
that Sam could meet
himself a gospel singer.

07:13.421 --> 07:15.480
I heard the whole
family sing at Chene Park.

07:15.525 --> 07:17.741
- Beautiful.
- So talented.

07:17.773 --> 07:19.541
- Mm-hmm.
- Yeah, yeah,

07:19.575 --> 07:21.210
but there's really no way to tell.

07:21.243 --> 07:23.768
I mean, it's not like you
can boo a gospel singer.

07:25.637 --> 07:27.896
No, she's... she is so nice.

07:28.117 --> 07:31.053
She's lovely, lovely.

07:31.086 --> 07:34.034
But did anybody taste

07:34.059 --> 07:36.090
the potato salad she brought?

07:36.558 --> 07:38.761
I mean, I don't want to say it's bland,

07:38.794 --> 07:40.596
but I saw a fly land on it,

07:40.933 --> 07:42.611
fly away, come back with some salt.

07:42.611 --> 07:45.285
Tim! You're bad.

07:45.581 --> 07:47.383
Potato salad?
More like "poor" -tato salad.

07:47.416 --> 07:49.467
Yeah.

07:50.114 --> 07:52.054
Look, look, look on the bright side.

07:52.088 --> 07:54.356
At least we know Sam's
gonna lose some weight.

07:54.390 --> 07:56.471
Oh!

07:58.527 --> 08:00.062
Too much she can't lose any weight

08:00.096 --> 08:02.064
in that big ol' head of hers.

08:02.098 --> 08:04.100
Whoo!

08:04.133 --> 08:06.635
She walk by and I
thought it was an eclipse!

08:07.970 --> 08:10.423
Aunt Lacey! Aunt Lacey's joining!

08:10.423 --> 08:13.650
Let's just hope Sam
likes doing neck rubs,

08:13.675 --> 08:16.278
'cause that neck of
hers is doing some work.

08:16.311 --> 08:18.179
Yeah.

08:18.213 --> 08:20.682
Looking like a lollipop
in knockoff Ann Taylor.

08:20.715 --> 08:22.684
Yes! Yes, it is!

08:22.717 --> 08:24.085
- It's knockoff!
- I know.

08:26.688 --> 08:28.657
- Hey.
- Hi, Shannon. Hope you're having fun.

08:29.925 --> 08:31.960
So, really, I'm happy for Sam.

08:31.993 --> 08:33.828
She truly is a sweet girl.

08:33.861 --> 08:35.764
Yeah, no, she's so sweet.

08:35.797 --> 08:37.673
She's made of sugar. Hope it doesn't rain;

08:37.698 --> 08:39.639
she turns into a [BLEEP] puddle!

08:40.126 --> 08:41.177
Timothy.

08:41.202 --> 08:43.004
- That mouth.
- Mm-mm-mm.

08:43.038 --> 08:44.839
We were having fun,
but that's carrying it

08:44.873 --> 08:45.840
a little too far.

08:45.874 --> 08:47.137
I wasn't having fun.

08:47.982 --> 08:49.635
Enjoy your meals all mushed together.

08:52.047 --> 08:54.182
Sam. Congratulations on becoming

08:54.215 --> 08:55.545
grill master.

08:55.545 --> 08:56.985
Go ahead with your insult, Chrissy.

08:57.018 --> 08:59.054
- I don't have an insult.
- Why? Too dumb?

08:59.087 --> 09:00.889
- I'm just surprised.
- Damn it.

09:00.922 --> 09:02.624
You're brave enough to
take on this responsibility

09:02.657 --> 09:04.659
after you quit Dad's restaurant.

09:04.693 --> 09:06.673
I was 15.

09:06.717 --> 09:08.419
Nobody even cares about that anymore.

09:08.452 --> 09:09.643
Daddy cares.

09:09.643 --> 09:11.423
You quit the waffle
station right in the middle

09:11.455 --> 09:12.657
of Mothers' Day brunch.

09:12.690 --> 09:15.245
People just pouring syrup on waffle batter.

09:15.426 --> 09:17.799
- So sad.
- Dog food over there, Chrissy.

09:17.799 --> 09:19.067
Why don't you go eat up? Hey!

09:19.101 --> 09:20.435
Hurry it up up there!

09:20.469 --> 09:22.371
Whoo, you call this well-done?

09:22.720 --> 09:24.321
I took a bite out of it; it said,

09:24.355 --> 09:25.828
"Ouch, you hurting me!"

09:27.804 --> 09:30.618
She said it talked!

09:32.512 --> 09:34.083
Hey! Hey, you kids!

09:34.304 --> 09:36.039
Don't go wandering off in them woods.

09:36.479 --> 09:38.110
Might mess around and get snatched up

09:38.110 --> 09:39.170
by the Fork Bandit!

09:39.468 --> 09:41.450
Y'all don't know who the Fork Bandit is?

09:41.925 --> 09:43.612
They don't know who the Fork Bandit is.

09:43.723 --> 09:45.897
He was a kid, just like you.

09:46.126 --> 09:48.069
He wandered off from a barbecue,

09:48.295 --> 09:49.772
couldn't find his family,

09:49.772 --> 09:53.642
and now he's a dusty crackhead
with nothing but a fork!

09:53.676 --> 09:55.558
Anytime today, Sam.

09:56.035 --> 09:58.080
It's gonna be just a slight delay.

09:58.114 --> 09:59.648
Sam gotta speed up.

09:59.682 --> 10:01.784
This long line's driving me to drink.

10:02.157 --> 10:03.363
Driving me to drink.

10:03.388 --> 10:04.739
Hey, come on, now. Look here.

10:04.739 --> 10:06.741
This is a brand-new grill master.

10:07.096 --> 10:08.856
We gotta give him a chance to find his way.

10:08.856 --> 10:09.957
Flip six, son.

10:09.990 --> 10:11.826
- Uh, yeah.
- In a little while,

10:11.859 --> 10:13.294
he's gonna be out-grilling us all,

10:13.327 --> 10:14.662
providing he don't quit.

10:14.695 --> 10:16.526
I'm not going to quit, Dad.

10:16.551 --> 10:19.554
You're not again, because
now you are a grown man,

10:19.672 --> 10:22.639
and this is a responsibility.

10:23.793 --> 10:26.762
Son, get rid of eight and nine.

10:26.796 --> 10:27.941
They done.

10:28.692 --> 10:31.862
- Hey, grill master.
- Hey, baby.

10:31.895 --> 10:34.164
Mwah. Babe, look at us.

10:34.197 --> 10:36.520
I mean, me impressing your family,

10:36.567 --> 10:38.268
you're grill master.

10:38.587 --> 10:40.070
We're the hits of this party, babe.

10:40.368 --> 10:42.705
Yep, everybody loves us and
is happy with our performance.

10:42.739 --> 10:44.908
That they are, and that they do.

10:45.181 --> 10:46.616
- Give it to me.
- Mwah.

10:47.073 --> 10:49.000
Hey, Shannon. Can I get a picture?

10:49.419 --> 10:50.875
I have something better for you.

10:52.088 --> 10:54.391
♪ Leave a message ♪

10:54.424 --> 10:55.585
♪ God is good ♪

10:55.585 --> 10:57.153
Whoo!

10:57.687 --> 10:58.908
For when they call.

10:58.908 --> 10:59.876
Hey, guys!

11:00.268 --> 11:01.917
There's paper bowls here.

11:01.917 --> 11:03.204
New this year.

11:03.238 --> 11:05.046
Good for dip, sides, whatever.

11:05.071 --> 11:07.154
Look kind of fun. Try 'em out.

11:08.543 --> 11:10.445
No bowl, sweetie?

11:10.478 --> 11:11.840
No bowls.

11:12.281 --> 11:15.503
- Who's this?
- My friend from school, Evan.

11:15.985 --> 11:17.962
- How you doing, Evan?
- Tim Cramblin. Cramblin Advertising.

11:17.962 --> 11:19.797
- You want to hear a joke?
- No, I don't.

11:20.454 --> 11:22.774
I just don't think a little kid's joke

11:22.774 --> 11:24.743
is ever going to make
me, an adult man, laugh.

11:25.459 --> 11:28.046
Thanks, though. Just don't
have the life experience.

11:28.080 --> 11:29.639
- Thank you.
- Hey, Uncle Tim?

11:29.717 --> 11:31.016
Yes, sweetie?

11:31.049 --> 11:32.497
Sometimes I think things

11:32.522 --> 11:34.091
but I don't say them out loud,

11:34.124 --> 11:35.425
'cause then people hear them

11:35.459 --> 11:36.860
and they might hurt their feelings.

11:40.991 --> 11:42.156
Oh, my God.

11:43.248 --> 11:44.636
I am harsh.

11:45.738 --> 11:46.978
I'm harsh!

11:47.641 --> 11:48.625
Thank you.

11:50.187 --> 11:52.042
Ooh.

11:55.742 --> 11:56.980
It's okay, son. I got this.

11:57.014 --> 11:58.082
Don't worry about a thing.

11:58.415 --> 11:59.930
Ah, Sam.

12:04.277 --> 12:05.522
You got divorced.

12:05.555 --> 12:07.157
You're not in the family anymore.

12:07.190 --> 12:08.598
You got to give up that shirt.

12:08.623 --> 12:09.621
Chrissy.

12:10.527 --> 12:13.030
I am so sorry I called
your family pig-faced liars.

12:13.063 --> 12:14.979
Mm, thank you, baby.

12:14.979 --> 12:17.015
And I'm sorry I said
[BLEEP] in front of your mom.

12:17.529 --> 12:18.849
- You did?
- Yeah.

12:19.128 --> 12:20.806
And Aunt Lacey and Old Shirley.

12:21.691 --> 12:23.326
But I'm not that person anymore.

12:23.855 --> 12:25.141
I am harsh.

12:25.819 --> 12:27.374
I realize that now.

12:27.374 --> 12:30.507
It took a weird little kid with
a shitty joke I never heard,

12:30.532 --> 12:32.011
but I'm gonna be a better man.

12:32.621 --> 12:33.687
I love you so much.

12:33.687 --> 12:35.990
- Mm.
- I love you too, baby.

12:38.092 --> 12:40.326
Hey, girl! I like that hat.

12:41.522 --> 12:43.157
Have fun, everybody.

12:43.190 --> 12:44.451
Oh, and Sam?

12:44.758 --> 12:46.560
Take it easy on your daddy.

12:46.593 --> 12:48.662
I need him in tip-top shape today.

12:48.695 --> 12:50.965
Oh! Gross! Mom!

12:50.966 --> 12:52.766
Hey, be happy for me.

12:52.800 --> 12:54.343
I'm gonna let you take it out first.

12:54.568 --> 12:56.608
'Cause you're gonna need
all the help you can get.

12:57.902 --> 12:59.129
Let's ball.

12:59.606 --> 13:00.741
What you got, Sam?

13:00.774 --> 13:01.937
What you got, bro?

